'''Primarius''' is a Latin term referring to "one of the first, of the first rank, chief, principal, excellent, remarkable"<ref>Charlton T. Lewis, Ph.D. and. Charles Short, LL.D., ''A Latin Dictionary,'' Clarendon Press, Oxford, 1879. ISBN 0198642016.</ref>  It was used as the title of a position in universities.

